  "description": "For more information about this data see the publication: https://doi.org/10.1038/s41587-024-02245-9\n\nThe publication GitHub is a good source of information: https://github.com/UK-SBCoA-EbbertLab/brain_cDNA_discovery\n\nThere are also README files in the data that provide more information about what is contained in each directory.\n\n\u00a0\n\nBasic information about main directory structure and files:\n\nreproducing_RNA_figures - Contains all references/annotations necessary for reproducing the stats, analysis, and figures for the RNA isoform analysis in the article.\n\nreproducing_nextflow_pipeline - Contains all references/annotations necessary for reproducing the NextFlow pipeline.\n\nproteomics - Fasta reference files files used for proteomics analysis with FragPipe and results output by FragPipe.\n\ntranscriptomic_analysis_output - Contains output from transcriptomic analysis including: quality control, counts matrices, new RNA isoform annotations, and the Bambu R object.\n\ncounts_transcript.txt - Transcript level counts (does not include any intronic reads).",
